*Smarter Surge Management for Real-World Conditions*


Operations don=E2=80=99t just depend on days, times, or dates =E2=80=94 wea=
ther plays a
major role too. Rain often slows down movement on the ground, increases
rider effort, and impacts fulfillment reliability.

To help networks better manage these conditions, we=E2=80=99re introducing =
a new
way to configure surges that respond to real-time challenges.
*Why We Built This*

Previously, surge rules could only be created based on *Days, Time, and
Date*. But weather-based variations remained unsupported, making it harder
to adjust charges dynamically during rain.

With *Rain Surge*, you can ensure riders are compensated fairly and
operational costs are balanced, without manual intervention or guesswork.

This leads to:

=E2=80=A2 Better rider satisfaction during tougher delivery conditions

=E2=80=A2 More accurate cost allocation

=E2=80=A2 Reduced need for reactive, ad-hoc adjustments
What=E2=80=99s New


Rain Surge

A new *Rain* tab is now available under the Surge Pricing section.

Here, network owners/managers can define two simple fields:

=E2=80=A2 *Percentage* =E2=80=93 Surge percentage to apply during rain.

=E2=80=A2 *Flat Rate* =E2=80=93 A fixed amount added on top just like other=
 surge types.

The system will automatically apply the *maximum applicable charge* whereve=
r
overlaps occur. If nothing is defined in the Rain tab, *no rain surge* will
be applied by default.
What This Mean To You


With this update, network owners and managers can now set up *Rain
Surge* directly
within the Surge pricing section, giving you more control and smarter
pricing during weather-impacted hours.
What=E2=80=99s Next


We=E2=80=99re working on something that will give you far greater control o=
ver how
surges behave across different days and dates, allowing you to design
patterns and exceptions that match your network=E2=80=99s unique rhythm.


Soon, you=E2=80=99ll be able to set up surge rules that feel almost =E2=80=
=9Cintelligent,=E2=80=9D
adapting themselves to the way your operations move.

More flexibility. More precision.
And a whole new level of control is just around the corner.
